# Hotel Management System Frontend

This project is a frontend application for a hotel management system. It is built using Python and utilizes the Flask web framework to serve dynamic content and static files.

flask framework is used for python frontend framework development and API's. different from HTML as it basically instead of displaying on a browser. it generates a python server to which the app runs on.
NB: sometimes you require to kill a process in that is using the port designated for that task you do this by the command sudo kill -9 <PID> which is the activity number of the port. to getther pid number of the port you run sudo lsof -i : 5000 

## Project Structure

```
hotel-management-frontend
├── src
│   ├── main.py               # Entry point of the application
│   ├── templates
│   │   └── index.html        # Main HTML page
│   ├── static
│   │   ├── css
│   │   │   └── styles.css    # CSS styles for the frontend
│   │   └── js
│   │       └── scripts.js     # JavaScript for client-side functionality
├── requirements.txt          # Project dependencies
└── README.md                 # Project documentation
```
